    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>N Orls</placeName>
                <date>May 8. 5611</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I believe I have not as yet<lb/> acknowledged yours of <date>Feby
                    19.</date> and<lb/> in good earth even more I have nothing<lb/> worthy of time
                to write to you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send you by mail to day the<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Picayune</hi> of last <date>Saturday 3d.</date> Inst<lb/> in
                which you will find the paragraph<lb/> which I enclose for fear that the<lb/>
                newspaper may not reach you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our mutual friend <persName>Gutheim</persName> asked<lb/> me to
                write a few lines about<lb/> you and have it inserted in the<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Picayune</hi> which I did with pleasure,<lb/> and the thought
                just came to me<lb/> that he asked me to send you a copy<lb/> of the paper. Perhaps
                he may have<lb/> also sent the paper.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As to your late congregation,<lb/> or a majority of them, I hold
                them<lb/> in too little esteem even to say<lb/> a few words about them. Let<lb/>
                them alone and their insignificance</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>will be the sooner <sic>discoverd</sic>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We are getting along shortly<lb/> here, the people are lukewarm<lb/>
                and pernicious, and a few have<lb/> to stand the lament of expense,<lb/> in our
                congregation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Things did look very squally<lb/> at the date of <persName>Mr.
                    Touro's</persName> last<lb/> letter to you, but I am happy<lb/> to say that
                things look a<lb/> good deal better now.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As the <persName role="author">revd. Nathan</persName> has just<lb/>
                this moment come in my office<lb/> I shall make him fill the<lb/> rest of this
                sheet</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am my dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">yours ever faithfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Gershom K</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="Note:"> The following is a clipping from the <hi rend="underline">Picayune</hi>
                that is attached to page 2.</p>
            <p>luc, <persName>Genibrel</persName>, <persName>Graat</persName> and
                    <persName>Scott</persName> in the chief charac-<lb/> ters.</p>
            <p>———</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">TOKEN OF RESPECT.—We see the Hebrew<lb/> congregation in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> have presented the<lb/>
                <persName>Rev. Isaac Leeser</persName>, who has been their pastor for<lb/>
                twenty-one years, with an elegant service of plate,<lb/> consisting of a pair of
                pitchers, a pair of salvers,<lb/> and half a dozen goblets, all of the most
                splendid<lb/> workmanship. Suitable inscriptions express the<lb/> high appreciation
                which the donors have of the<lb/> abilities and labors of their minister. The
                    <persName>Rev.<lb/> Mr. Leeser</persName> is the editor of the “Occident,”
                and<lb/> the important services which he has rendered to<lb/> his brethren in this
                country are, we believe, uni-<lb/>versally admitted.</p>
            <p>———</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">NEW MUSIC.—We have received the following<lb/> from <persName>Tyler
                    &amp; Hewitt</persName>, <placeName>No. 39 Camp <sic>street</sic></placeName>:
                Xaupi's</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <sic>Dearfriend</sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I owe you a letter a long time, but<lb/> really had so little to
                communicate of a pleasant nature, and felt<lb/> so undesirous of making any comments
                on the proceedings of the<lb/> cabal formed against you, or the lukewarmness shown
                by such as<lb/> profess themselves your friends, in not breaking it up, that I had
                no<lb/> heart for doing what at another time would have been a pleasure.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have seven subscribers on my list, whose names I will<lb/> send
                you in a few days. The most of them are for the <hi rend="underline">Bible</hi>
                and<lb/> the advocate both. There is little spirit in my congregation; but<lb/> when
                the Bible is completed, I have little doubt of being able to<lb/> dispose of many
                copies; its price $6 deters many from subscribing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is useless expatiating on my troubles; I have<lb/> become callous
                to them, and am determined not to worry myself<lb/> to neutralize the malicious
                efforts of discontented demagogues against<lb/> me. As long as I can <add>?</add>
                this place, I continue in my office,<lb/> when no longer practicable—away with bib
                and gown—and<lb/> hurra for something more congenial and less annoying.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I will most certainly write you again shortly.<lb/> I congratulate
                you on the handsome testimonial of respect you<lb/> have recd. and the address which
                must be still more satisfactory.<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Desiring</hi> you to be well and happy which <persName>Mrs.
                    N</persName> wish her love, also<lb/> does <hi rend="indent(7)">I am</hi></p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your's Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">MNN.</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penna</placeName>
            </p>
